 n! = \int_0^\infty x^{n}e^{-x}dx 
 =\left[-x^{n}e^{-x}\right]^{\infty}_{0}-\int_0^\infty -nx^{n-1}e^{-x}dx\, 
 =-\infty^{n}e^{-\infty}-(-0^{n}e^{-0})-(-n)\int_0^\infty x^{n-1}e^{-x}dx 
 =n\int_0^\infty x^{n-1}e^{-x}dx 
 =n(n-1)! 
\Gamma(n) = (n-1)!
x=1,2,3,\ldots
\frac12
(-\frac12)! =\Gamma(\frac12)=\sqrt{\pi}
x\Gamma(x)=\Gamma(x+1)
n(n-1)!=n!
